data.name: FIRE BOROUGH
data.description:
Located to the south of the region. It's the capital of Motley Land due to its comercial and economical relevance. Even if it's the biggest city, it's not the most populated cause people moved to Leaf Village two decades ago, searching a healthier and more natural environment, running away form the pandemic. Now, just a few workers of the metal industry remain here.
Temperature increased significantly these past ten years, so only those creatures who can resist extreme heat and scarce water supply can stay here.

Fire Borough residents hate random sh*tty NFT airdrops (unless its fine art, of course)

Stake Farms Company‚Ñ¢ has proudly the higher interest rate protocol to stake your coins in Motley Land.

data.name: ICE CREEK
data.description:
This small and cold town is located to the north of the region. Its mountains get slammed with snow almost all year round. Ice Creek main activity focuses on scientific research, and it has numerous laboratories dedicated to investigate animals and plants, climate phenomenons and global warming, future technologies and astronomy.

It has the biggest Global Seed Vault in the planet, to secure a backup of the whole world's crop diversity.

There aren't so much living organisms in this region since robots took over a couple years ago, where they work doing research and hard jobs like snowplowing, glowing up the place (because it's dark the half of the year), keep safety on the streets, bureaucracy stuff...

Illustration and animation by JORDI GANDUL
Collect any piece of this collection and get the free Augmented Reality fine art print (38x38cm)

data.name: LEAF VILLAGE
data.description:
Leaf Village is the people's favourite place to live. Famous for farming and agriculture, its vegetables are the healthiest and most delicious you can eat.
Located in the middle of Motley Land, it's a nice urban space, surrounded by green areas and very pure air. It's the most populated city of this country since two decades ago, a pandemic hit the whole region but this city. Some scientific studies proved that the air and the lifestyle of this place was protecting and keeping their residents healthy and everyone wanted to move there. Houses started to get unaffordable due to the heavy Real Estate demand and pollution was rising until the government created some laws to protect the environment, creating eco-buildings, and banning gas-powered vehicles.

It only uses renewable energy from solar panels and wind power.

Leaf Creek healing properties are well known, so they built the ''Nifty ward'', where patients are seeing a significant improvement in their health by just living there.

data.name: Tired Putto
data.description:
In the third couple, I used the color Blue, starting from the expression "Blue Monday". In the first picture, there's a putto, that even if able to use that instrument in the right way by blowing in it,  is now using it as a cane; While in the second one, Blue is used to enhance the springs, very useful mechanical objects, now used to let two apparently useless rocks rest.
I relate those pictures to the expression "Blue Monday" because, as in those pictures these tools are used improperly, as during any "Blue Monday" we use our mind in the wrong way, because we forget that sadness or "the blue feeling", is just a result of the inappropriate way to use our tool, our mind.

data.name: Venezuela fight for liberty
data.description:
After years of shortages, inflation, insecurity and attacks on critical thinking, the people of Venezuela decided that the government of Nicolas Maduro was illegitimate. The streets of Caracas and the principal cities of the country starts to get full of angry people tired of the current situation. The regime was violent and strongly repressed the protests where thousands were injured and there were dozens of deaths.

This work means a lot to me, as a press photographer, I was attacked by the national guard who shot me a few meters away, causing a broken leg. Months later, I was again persecuted by the political police of the Maduro regime for which I fled my country.

data.name: Coronal Mass Ejection
data.description:
A collection exploring some possible Great Filters of the Fermi Paradox.

As this civilization entered its technology area.  More and more power and information cables where set up around the planet.  This coil of cable can interact with magnetic objects like the sun.  With a large and unluckily directed coronal mass ejection. magnetically interacted and created a massive current that ran through the network, destroying every device on the power grid. Without communications production and transportation the civilization fell rapidly and was never able to recover. Stars may not be as stable over long times as we have though a coronal mass ejection could be in our future as well.

data.name: Dancing with the Shadow
data.description:
Everyone of us has both the light and their dark shadows.
It‚Äôs said that the people are led by the light or the darkness within them when doing something that can influence others or when making a choice.

When being led by the light it is logical to act and to speak relying on our hearts, consciousness and morality that usually spreads kindness, love and positivity.

But sometimes the shadows appear. They are those negative thoughts and emotions that are usually assigned to a devilish behavior and that lead us to act and to speak being on the hook of our bile. It doesn‚Äôt only spread negativity around and causes pain but also poisons our souls and displaces the light within us.

‚ÄúDancing with the Shadow‚Äù is an artwork dedicated to our inner power to control the shadows, to stop them from leading us and start leading them, make them follow the dance of consciousness with us and to turn them into something beautiful.

An original digital hand drawn painting

data.name: Salvation

There‚Äôs always someone that can become a ray of the sun for you. There‚Äôs always a piece of hope, no matter how deformed your inner self is.

data.name: Two-headed wise crow
data.description:
I compare Istanbul to this two-headed crow. A wise crow, one side in europe but its real essence and body in asia.

I am an Istanbul photographer. These streets are my studio and my material. Therefore, every single work of mine revolves around and relates to Istanbul. As I walk the streets of this city, I find myself choosing between old and new, beautiful or ugly, love and hate. I take pictures using only my muscle memory and index finger and not fearing my mistakes and accidents, in fact learning from them.

data.name: hands, only hands
data.description:
Hands. Perfect balance, tools of our mind. 
Hands are the most frequently symbolized parts of the human body and they help us communicate.

Hands are not really weapons of seduction, but their soft touch can trigger our desires. They have the power to excite. 
Imagine a woman caressing her neck, imagine that hand sliding on her breast. What if she brings her hand to you? Hands are always the first physical contact.

When you get people's attention using hands, only hands, you're doing it right.

data.name: Frozen Lake
data.description:
Fri, Mar 25, 2022 - 18:28

The day before, we took a bullet train from Berlin to Garmisch-Partenkirchen, a small town in the southern part of Germany, rented a cozy place for us, and spent our weekend amidst the German mountains. The whole scenery was stunning, we were surrounded by mountains. 

We rented a car on the second day and drove to the Eibsee, a lake in Bavaria, Germany, just 9 km away from where we stayed. When we got there, the sun was just setting, and the lake was still frozen. The temperature was rather cool, but one could still feel a little bit of warmth from the setting sun. 

The whole journey was tremendous, but it was only the beginning.


Love,
Chisa

data.name: SERVAL
data.description:
SERVAL

by Brad Wilson

Edition 1/1

6000 x 6000 px

The serval (Leptailurus serval)¬†is a wild cat that lives in most areas of sub-Saharan Africa.

2022 IUCN conservation status: Least concern¬†

These in-studio, high-resolution photographs show the rarest moment captured with each animal‚Äìthe direct frontal gaze‚Äìsomething that happened for only a few seconds over the course of many hours. This fleeting eye contact offers a powerful sense of intimacy, connection and authentic encounter‚Äìan experience not normally possible in the wild, or even in captive settings. 

The images have been featured by Audubon, World Wildlife Fund, Greenpeace, Microsoft and Apple. The work has been widely exhibited and sold in the US, Europe and Asia, and is in numerous private and institutional collections.

A signed copy of my book, ‚ÄúTHE OTHER WORLD,‚Äù will be included with each sale.

Long road. Another country. But the horror of what is happening is the same. Hatred for all Russians who are involved in the war. 
I want to back home. There are my family and loved ones. There, at home - war. 
While we are here, we will help our country win.

Glory to Ukraine! I will definitely come back home.

data.name: Eternity
data.description:
Resolution: 4583 x 4993 | Medium: Oil on Canvas

The Plastic Age series has been exhibited internationally including showings in the USA, Taiwan, and Europe. All artworks in this collection are originals created by renowned artist, C.J. Yeh. Every files was digitally optimized for large-scale printing or projection.

Yeh is a tenured professor of Art & Design at State University of New York. In this series, Yeh manually painted repetitive imageries in the same indifferent and faithful manner how you would ‚Äúcut and paste‚Äù pixels on a computer. It was Yeh‚Äôs process of trying to resolve the conflicts between his fascination with new media and his classic training as a painter. While the medium is traditional, the aesthetics embedded in these paintings are digital. What is most striking is the intricacy of play between conflicting images, which Yeh uses to redefine dignity as an honest and unflinching vision turned toward one‚Äôs self.

data.name: Big Freedia, RVA.mem 2016
data.description:
Composition derived from three images taken at:

Big Freedia
featuring Tank and the Bangas and Deep Velvet
October 15, 2016
at Strange Matter in Richmond, VA

---

The air conditioner at Smatter was still broken and it was humid and sweaty. This show was completely packed. As short as I am, the only way I got this shot was by pressing through the crowd and standing on the stairs that lead from the floor to the stage, snapping this while she was walking through the crowd (they never had a green room) and then getting the hell out of her way. She passes through her crowds like royalty. The absolute frenzy of her fans shooting video as she walked within inches of them was electric.

---

I capture things the way I remember them: non-linear time in blurs of intense kinetic energy, sound, and emotion.

Captured here:
Elation
Frenzy
Delirium
Awe
Overwhelm

by Wesley McQuillen

data.description: Having gone a certain way in life, we come to understand that the world around us is not three-dimensional. data.name: Integrity

It is a complete merging with the world, a free letting through of different energies for experience, cognition, exploration without evaluation of these energies, a state of being a Creator Man.  The soul blossoms and develops, feels joy and fullness, accesses its talents and inner power.  Only now with wholeness do I understand myself, see my path clearly and accept the world and othe

data.name: Acceptance
data.description: Acceptance is a new level of understanding. Understanding that everything that happened to me is necessary for something. Understanding that the problem always comes from within me outward and manifests itself through external circumstances. I always get what I broadcast to the World. And the external World signals me through the situation what to pay attention to in ME. And a very important understanding is that to accept the situation is not to accept the unfairness of what is happening to you, it is not to submit to the circumstances. Every situation contains a "pearl of wisdom. What happened gives me a reason to reflect on why this situation happened to me and to see what important things it highlights. By thanking everyone involved in the events, one must see the depth and wisdom in each step. By learning to accept, one becomes a more harmonious person.

data.name: Bull Run
data.description:
My first experiment with animated patterns reimagines the term 'bull run' using the bull skull of the revered Ankole cow from eastern and central Africa. The Ankole cow is a large beast that can grow up to 7ft tall and is known known for having majestic long horns, which can sometimes grow up to 1.8m (6ft.) long! For many of the communities that own them, the cows hold special significance. Traditional Ankole ceremonies often have dancers with their hands twisting in the air mimicking the shape of the horns on their cattle. For the Mundari community in Sudan, herdsmen often grow very strong bonds to their herd - often naming them and pampering them however they can.

This piece was minted as part of the inaugural fwb Fellowship collection. The sale of 'Bull Run' will fund and unlock a further 7 pieces in this collection.

Dimensions: 1500px x 1500px

data.name: ‚ÄúCan you see me now?‚Äù
data.description:
This piece tries to capture how consuming the chase of visibilty is as a creator. Inspired by my experience with the pursuit of external validation, which started out slowly and harmlessly but began to fester and eclipse every single one of my achievements. 

It is a damaging thing, never being satisfied, no matter what stage you are at in your journey. And I had to realise a big part of the problem was that I was projecting my insecurities onto everyone else when it was me who struggled to validate myself.

I had to ask when it would ever be enough for me to see myself, as an artist on a journey. To see that I was getting up everyday and making a real effort.

The first collector of this digital piece will receive an exclusive 36‚Äù x 27‚Äù metal print delivered anywhere in the world.

data.name: The Black Reputation
data.description: It all started in my early childhood when I spotted a black cat in the middle of a playground. I hurled a small stone to shoo it away, partly out of fear. The cat fled, and as I reached the spot where the feline was seated, I found a two Rupee coin. Extremely thrilled and happy with my newfound treasure, I bought myself a bar of chocolate. The next day, the same cat was nowhere to be found. I, however, got fixated on the idea that if you spot a black cat, it will definitely bring you some good luck. Many years later, I was running extremely late for a flight, when a black cat crossed my path as I rode on the pillion. Without a doubt, I felt assured that good luck was to follow. To my disbelief, the repercussions of reaching late had me miss the flight and experience a very difficult afternoon. An acquaintance later highlighted that I shouldn't have let the feline cross the road. It struck me then. How could a creature hold a bad reputation for crossing the road?

data.name: The Black Reputation
data.description: Do we know why we have let the color of their skin become attached to such misguided notions of superstition? And why have we blindly followed them, only to add to the horrific mistreatment of these harmless creatures? With this installation, I have tried to recapture a moment of my childhood and present this clowder of black cats in front of you to stun you, confuse you, and convince you that there is no such thing as good bad luck. Today, you can either choose to walk past your fears by walking through this path or continue to live with them. Because if you've given a black cat the power to ruin your day, the joke is on you.

data.description:
This collection of 1/1 archive photographs of New York is a visual celebration of my 20+ years lived in this city: Its multitudes, its extraordinary scenes, and its staggering architecture, as well as a quiet elegy to its decay and rebirth.

This collection strives to be a token of sincere gratitude from the eyes of a Turkish immigrant, whose youth revolved around a deep fascination with American pop culture in the 1980s and 1990s, and a longing to belong to this city of neon and chrome.

data.name: Friend in an abandoned house
data.description:
On my way home from school, I was walking that day using a different road than usual. It was an abandoned house on a quiet, secluded alley, with a battered wooden exterior and open doors and windows, so it was easy to get inside.

 I checked around in the dimly lit room until my eyes adjusted, and then I saw something white out of the corner of my eye and turned around. 
I was relieved to find nothing.

Then I heard footsteps tapping on the stairs near the entrance, and as I hurried over, I heard a child laughing.
I wanted to have the place to myself, but there was no point if there were other guests ahead of me.
With a sigh and a slump of the shoulders, I was about to leave the abandoned house when...

"Hey."

I heard a voice behind me and turned to see a girl about my age.

.
.
.

data.name: Dark 06
data.description:
Throughout our lives we are forced to make a certain choice, it permeates our existence, because we are preconditioned to categorise everything on black and white, good and bad, beautiful and ugly. Such categories greatly limit our perception of reality. 

Despite our tendency to embrace discrete evaluation, life isn‚Äôt a fight between two extremes, which it seems to be. 

Instead, it appears as a subtle and fragile balance between elements, existing in everlasting symbiosis with each other. 

The material chosen for the visualisation of a futuristic hero appears as an organic glass, ephemeral and fragile garment, just like our own idea of reality, representing the concept of eternal balance. Its transparency depicts the purity of a hero and reflections appear as a soul mirror. The hero finds himself in both light and dark, depending on the light scene. Optical diffractions and contrasting backgrounds serve as transitional stages in attempts to grasp the essence of reality.

data.name: Èõ∑Á•û„ÄÄRAIJIN
data.description:
RAIJIN Raijin
A deity that deifies thunder. Names such as Raiden-sama, Narukami, Dondo-kami, Hata-kami, Inazuma-sama, Ikazuchi, and Kaminari are often based on the sound of thunder and lightning. As a water god and fire god, the thunder god was regarded as a mediator between heaven and earth, and thunder also meant the manifestation of a deity, as in the name Kandachi.
Benefits
Many shrines worship the god of thunder to pray for thunder and water disasters, and for a bountiful harvest of crops, and some have "Raijin" in the company name.

Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)

data.name: Ëø¶Ê•ºÁæÖ„ÄÄKARURA
data.description:
Sakyamuni What god?
Image search results for "What is Kalora?
Karura is a Buddhist patron deity, predecessor of the Indian mythology of Garuda. He was a member of the Eight Divisions and later the Twenty-eight Divisions. The phonetic transcription of "Karura" comes from the Pali language. He is also called Sakyamuni Buddha or King Sakyamuni.
He is the incarnation of a holy bird that devours all evil and runs in the sky.
Benefit
In Buddhism, the viper is considered to be an evil dragon that causes rain and wind and is a symbol of vexation, so it is believed to be a bird of gratitude that devours all evil. Because of its nature of devouring evil things, it is said to ward off strange diseases and prolong life. It is also believed to be beneficial for praying for rain and stopping rain.

data.name: Blue Glitch 1 - Cosmic Reunion
data.description:
"
I don‚Äôt know how some people find me. Sometimes I try to reach out
by jumping through spaces and forums. Other times I quack to spill
my mind to the meta world. Every action leads to equal reaction,
and every connection comes with its own noise. That‚Äôs what
normally happen everyday, that‚Äôs how I hustle to get discovered.
Then comes the time when the cosmos simply leads us towards one
another. That is the best kind of connection. Something genuine
and positive, and I feel like we are having a reunion. Like we are
just old friends from our previous life and we are so excited to meet
again.
"

data.name: Blue Glitch 2 - Ocean of Love
data.description:
"
When I think about this project, I think about my family. Being in
the NFT world has changed the life of me, my wife, and my baby
boy. If there is something I can give to them, it is an ocean of love
where we can forever be with each other. That is why I pour the
same ocean to this project. Because I believe love is the core of it all. I
am not naive. We need wealth and reputation to survive in the art
scene. But only through integrity and sincere connection, money
and fame becomes a meaningful legacy. And when I am gone, I
want people to know me as a loving person.
"

The backstory of this piece is quite devastating for me. "Blue Glitch" series is what I thought to be a life-changing commission, but turns out I was fooled.

data.name: Blue Glitch 3 - Sharkaurus Rex
data.description:
"
In a place full of artists and collectors, we tend to discover our personal sharks. These are people and entities who keep us on edge; making sure our creations are fresh and our mind stays clear. The sharks then meet with the Rex we kept inside, merging and turning into the vicious beast we need to tame. If we fail, we will perish, but if we are able to conquer this hybrid brute, it becomes a mighty generator that pushes us further and further.
"

The backstory of this piece is quite devastating for me. "Blue Glitch" series is what I thought to be a life-changing commission, but turns out I was fooled.

data.name: Road Of One Color
data.description:
Photo with history. With the arrival of covid-19, I was forced to leave the usual photo studio where I worked. I equipped a space for photography at home and began to create lighting fixtures using plastic, cardboard, clothespins, ropes, filters, various construction lamps and self-designed devices. It was a real laboratory of light. I painted the walls in 6 colors. I did not go to Paris for my birthday, but spent all my savings on a new studio.
This photo was taken in the first photo shoot in the new space. I, this day, changed about 15 lighting options. And I liked this color the most. I started using it more and more often after that. This photo was the beginning of many photo shoots where there was only one color.
If it weren't for that, my path would turn in the other direction. Whether it was good or bad, I don't know. But because of this portrait, I was stuck in one color for a long time.

Lviv, Ukraine
March, 2020

data.name: Adobe
data.description:
In 2018, I photographed a very cheaper camera. I dreamed of being an artist and a fashion photographer. I led an ascetic life. All the money I managed to save, I spent on the studio, the model's fee and props for photo shoots. At that time I had no opportunity to buy a professional camera, because I didn't even have enough money to live in Ukraine. Only a miracle could help me.

I really wanted the models in my photos to be the most beautiful. But since I was a beginner they didn't want photographed free. That day I paid the model my last money, because I really dreamed that she was in my photos. This was the main thing for me and brought me more joy than anything.

And a couple of months later a miracle happened! I posted a few photos on the Behance website. Adobe wanted to use this photo in one of its videos and offered me $ 1,000 for it. After that I borrowed more money and bought a professional photographic equipment.

Lviv, Ukraine
October, 2018
3456‚Ää√ó‚Ää5184px, jpg

data.name: Fight For Art
data.description:
Photo with history. This photo was taken the day after I bought my first camera in January 2019. Before that, I used my friend's amateur camera. I had fire in my eyes. I had a motto - Fight for art, and it remains.
Then I assembled a team and we shot my first fashion editorial. This story was published in the New York online magazine KUNST. It was very prestigious to get into it. After that, my life changed. I was noticed and began to cooperate with me. Models who previously ignored my requests for cooperation - began to be photographed for free.
This photo is very significant and important for me.
When I was taking this photo, I noticed that model Sofia can close one eye very well. I asked to do this several times on camera. My friends initially doubted this photo, but I believed in it to the last and continue to believe in it and in my motto - Fight for art!


Lviv, Ukraine
February, 2019

data.name: Nanogenesis
data.description: Monolithic nanoporous metal foams constitute a broad class of materials with unique structure and properties. The structure resembles a disordered three-dimensional maze of condensed open cells where relatively thick ligaments interconnect with massive nodes. Voids and matter are very close to each other on the nanometre scale, giving rise to two bi-continuous, complementary networks. The intricate architecture is the result of the atomic-scale selective dissolution of less noble chemical elements from Au-based binary or multinary alloys. Proceeding gradually via the removal of individual atoms from the alloy surface and the subsequent rearrangement of neighbouring sites, dealloying eventually induces deep changes in the surface morphologies and the local degree of porosity. The resulting structure consists of solid ligaments and nodes that have characteristic lengths reduced down to the nanometre size, which imparts on the material intriguing physical and chemical properties.

An ode to an old friend.

This lighthearted piece resonates with me deeper than the initial laugh. While drawing this piece I found myself consumed in appreciation. data.name: peace2711
data.description:
Series:
‚Äûpostcardsfromheaven‚Äú
The series is based on the series "the kodak moment". Postcards, in this case a selection of the issue nature, gardens, trees and parks, today only decoration in tourist shops were always greetings to home. A greeting to our loved ones and a hint that one has managed to get away once. Kitsch and an often stereotypical interpretation of landscape and nature have created an unbelievable collection of absurd impressions over the years. this absurdity is continued with the here shown images. New stories are told. Stories like postcards sent out of the world of dreams and fears. Stories with enigmatic humor and winking eyes. Surreal greetings from ‚ÄûAbsurdistan‚Äú. Humorous and serious contemplation of our past and present ..... fragments of history from a world that in and of itself is often completely out of joint.
Every picture represents a small intervention in nature. Barely noticeable or visibly easily are the wounds that were inflicted on this paradise.

data.name: Friend
data.description:
Unfortunately, the age of animals is short, and sooner or later each of us faces the bitterness of parting. When my dog died, for a long time it seemed that she was still around. I could hear her footsteps, see her shadow. Of course, it was all just a dream, but how real it felt, and how painful it was to realize that it was just a game of my imagination!
I think we owe animals a lot, because they are those sincere and kind creatures who give us emotional support no matter what kind of person you are. They love faithfully and sincerely.
This illustration was created from my own experiences. 
I often think about the fact that despite death, the dead are always there for us, looking at us and experiencing with us.
That's how the idea for this illustration was born

data.description:
In the summer of 2015 a tragicomic incident took place in the old town district of Istanbul. Due to an ordinary conflict, a tourist from Ireland fought many local men and beat them punching. He gained sympathy from a large part of society and was called the ‚ÄúIrish Tourist‚Äù and then the ‚ÄúIrish Boxer‚Äù.. For some he became a legend and even a hero because of beating bad guys. In time it was revealed that he was not Irish; but an Arabian man living in Ireland..

That incident was the source of inspiration while creating this artwork: The Irish Boxer is playing with his boxer puppy..

data.name: Just Me & You
data.description:
It‚Äôs just me and you tonight, isn‚Äôt that beautiful?

This photo was taken back in June 2020, in the heart of the pandemic.
Night clubs, events, amusement parks.. everything was closed off. The city was in complete lockdown.
As I was having a walk, I figured I‚Äôd stroll around near the Arch of Peace. It is usually one of the busiest areas since there‚Äôs many restaurants and parks around but that evening it was empty. Actually, quite scary I must say - never seen that place like that. As I was just going on the other side of the Arch I saw this couple, all alone.
Their voices were happy and loud. They were having a full-on dinner with pizza and beer. The guy has just finished pouring down the beer to the cup of his loved one and they ended up laughing in a very contagious way. In that moment everything almost felt normal again.

This photo was published on Italy‚Äôs most famous newspaper ‚Äò‚ÄôCorriere della Sera‚Äô‚Äô and on Sony Alpha‚Äôs website.

data.name: Divide
data.description:
When the energy of two waves reflects and refracts, moments like 'Divide' are created. 

One does not accidentally capture an image like this.

Sometimes years are spent chasing one fraction of a second. Travelling, searching, carrying bulky bags of camera equipment on and off planes, boats and helicopters, years of swimming with a camera in a waterproof housing - to seek out these moments of ephemerality.

Oce captured, this singular moment is then transformed into a mesmerizing moving image, detailing the ocean‚Äôs myriad of colours and textures, as well as its immense power.

INFINITY MATRIX

Inspired by the sensory experience of floral gardens, this work uses a potent colour field reminiscent of lavender. Overlaid with a repetition of meandering calligraphic strokes the 'garden' is depicted as if from an aerial perspective, and at once an olfactory one. 

The INFINITY MATRIX are abstractions of nature, space, time and the cosmic realm referred to in Chinese Daoist philosophy as the Dao (The Way). In these works I draw together modern abstraction with Chinese calligraphic strokes to create vast immersive spaces in which to mind wander within.

These works are formed through a hand painted automative repetition of 5 calligraphic strokes. These works act as a vehicle for connection between artist, audience and the metaphysical realm. They celebrate the power of art and its capacity to enhance human experience and consciousness.

data.name: Rewire old beliefs
data.description:
The Snake represents the negativity and disbelief that surrounds us. The representation of temptation can become part of your subconscious when you have to go through a healing path. When someone is discouraged, over and over again, your subconscious will get stuck in the wrong pattern, leading to self-sabotage. The healing comes when you rediscover yourself and listen to your intuition daily. A daily practice that brings you happiness can help you rewire the old pattern that unconsciously impacts your life.
The butterflies represent the possibility of you becoming happy and fulfilled. Butterflies symbolise spiritual rebirth, transformation, and change, but will you make space for them to heal you?
In my path, I have used mindfulness and numerology to rediscover myself and create space for transformation. 
And so, I decided to offer this artwork‚Äôs collector a personalised numerology reading and a personalised meditation to strengthen your inner power.

data.name: Dancer 1.01
data.description:
In movies that I make, I am sculpting in time. Like Tarkovsky who inspires me.

For the "Dancer Dots" digital art project, it was about scanning multiple portions of that time and then digging through that scan to find the best frame possible.

This frame was extracted from a LiDAR scanning session with Maya. It was then enhanced and color graded.

Maya is a contemporary dancer who explores the slow and the self. A constant and slow movement between the inside and the outside. Like a pendulum.

The core ideas of the project are:

- Show dance and movement differently, using technology.
- Giveback to the dancers and dance communities.
- As a collector, be an important part of a project (gifts, be a part of the creative process)
- Get enough funds to make a 3D animation short film with scanned dancers or collectors.
- Split the profits with everyone participating in this project (dancers, collectors, animators...etc.)

For more information, on this project: https://www.dancerdots.com/

data.name: USSR and French branch of a family (1986)
data.description:
During World War II, my grandfather Vasilii was recruited into the USSR army, and his brother (uncle Yasha) was forcibly recruited into Romanian army which was fighting on Germany side. Thus, they fought against each other.

Both survived. My grandfather returned to his native town Balti (currently - Moldova), and his brother settled in France. Only in 1986, when the Iron curtains almost fell, the descendants of the French branch were able to visit their historical homeland for the first time.

It was strange meeting of totally different cultures. Even on the photo you can see how different are my grandparents and their grand-nephews.

80 years after the war we, the descendants, still keep in touch and sometimes visit each other. Although we are totally different and even speak different languages.

The photo revives the history of individuals,  entire generations and countries.

data.name: Battle Lost
data.description:
An abandoned building in the former Packard Automotive Plant in Detroit Michigan, USA. On the horizon in the distance, the modern towers of the General Motors Corporation Headquarters are visible, a testimony to the winner in the battle for American luxury car manufacturing dominance.

Places and things abandoned are a statement of society‚Äôs tendency to move forward, to gravitate towards the new and shiny while leaving much of the old behind. They exhibit an inherent beauty that is mostly overlooked, relics of the past that are left to the elements and time to be reclaimed by nature. The Windows Forgotten collection by Trent North is comprised of 1/1 photos from unique locales around the world.

data.name: Controlled Desolation
data.description:
An abandoned passenger terminal on the banks of the Dniester River in Bender, Pridnestrovian Moldavian Republic (aka: Transnistria). This Soviet era river and sea cruise station was once a hallmark feature of the city. It now stands idle and in disrepair, a statement of another time in an unrecognized breakaway state within Moldova.

data.name: [Dungeon and Pepe] Episode 1/ Mandatory invitation
data.description:
Pepe is an informant in Famton, the country he is in, for the task given by the clan he has been in for a long time. Famton is a trading country.Pepe made a living there besides his job as an informant.Someone sat next to Pepe while he sipped his beer. As soon as this person sat next to him, he handed Pepe an envelope over the table and went to the bathroom. Pepe slowly opened the envelope and peered inside. Inside he saw a high-tech fiberglass chip with his clan's logo on it. The meaning of this chip was a sign that an important task was coming to Pepe. Pepe realized that he had to leave behind the order he had set up here and rushed to the bathroom. The man was not in the bathroom. Pepe took a long look at the chip.
1- Pepe activates the chip, listens and accepts the task.
2-Pepe throws the chip in the toilet and flushes it.
3-Pepe puts the chip in his pocket and heads home.
You can start the story by typing the number of the option you want to choose in the last digit of your offer.

data.name: INFAMOUS
data.description:
Prawle point has claimed many ships over the years due to its treacherous reefs. In December 1992 the ship Demetrios, formerly the Long Lin from China, was being towed by a tug from Dunkirk to a Mediterranean scrapyard. During big storms in the English Channel, the tow broke and the z drifted helplessly. The ship struck the rocks at Prawle Point on 18 December, breaking her back in a few hours. 

I‚Äôve had this image in mind for several years, but it was only recently, during Storm Eunice, that I managed to capture the shot I envisaged. I wanted to capture the treacherous reefs and the stormy seas. I was also lucky to include part of the Demetrios which is visible within the frame.

data.name: Fragmented #3
data.description:
‚ÄúFragmented‚Äù is a series inspired by a plate from my wife's late mother, Barbara. It broke in late 2020 and sat on our kitchen island for a few months because. I started to think about stories that could be told beyond the borders of the broken piece.

I moved the fragment to my studio where it stayed on an empty sheet of paper for weeks.

One day, I picked up a pen and started working on "Fragmented", exploring the possibilities of things broken and the stories that can evolve from them.

data.name: Supurbot
data.description:
We bought this Supurbot. So we liked it. Well, sir, what it does,  if there is a lot of work, it is self-replicating... Our house is 65m2, but we said, maybe we will get a big house in the future because they say the real estate bubble will burst in 2056, then we will have a nice house too. We said we'll use it then. 

We brought it, we put it, it actually cleans very well, but there is a problem. This thing multiplies! When it multiplies, it multiplies again! What am I suppose to do with so many robots bro? We gave them away to the neighbor, gave it to the relatives. A few months passed, everyone in the whole country became a robot owner. Everyone has finished the house work, they have their vineyards and gardens cleaned. Of course, there is no end to this work, those who escaped from the garden gates got involved in nature as well. They are spread over vast deserts. Big world my man, how cleaning can possibly end right?

data.name: Telebot
data.description:
It was a gift actually. We didn't bought it.Our house is full with better telescopes already.I kept thinking ''it wasn't necessary'' but, I don't know why, my daughter loved it! I saw them in the garden one day. While my girl was listening, it keeps telling something eagerly. Turns out, I didn't figure how to use this properly. If you don't ask It just reports ''Yeaa, it is a fine moon'' and shuts down.But if you ask properly, it tells you a long and a beatiful story.

I asked one day; ''can you go to the stars ?'' It said ''Yes,Of course^^''. 

After a while, we lost interest in it.One day, I realizd it was standng in the middle of our garden.It was its shooting position and eyes were missng.I took its controller and saw it.It was shooted to the stars! Who knows where it is now..I sat next to its empty body and realized two sad thngs. First, when the eyes come back, we will all be gone probably. Second and the worst, we are not going to be able to listen to its legendary journey ever.

data.name: Rock‚Äôn‚ÄôSmith
data.description:
The most famous Oscar ceremony clip in history, depicted in the simplest way possible: two sticks dancing around each other.

The primary purpose of this piece is to determine if the media, and the internet, have done a good enough job that almost anyone can recognize the reference clip when they see it.

The second purpose of this work is not to blame the actor for his act, but to point out what the media and the web are doing with it, and how fast and far things are going on the internet... without a very solid reason behind it.

data.name: IDENTITY
data.description:
Differences in facial details, body proportions and clothing are an important part of our physical and individual identities. It makes us recognizable and distinct, but all of these differences make a single collective identity when everything is put together and it could be seen as a species (human) or a nation or citizens of a city. In this video, I tried to show these individual differences at the same time as a single collective identity.
The video is made of repeating a 12-second loop that shows more than 100 faces, and you can see 15 different faces every second.

Director: Masoud Moein
Music Composer: Hootan Poorzaki
Produced by: 4rah Videos

data.name: Reclaimed
data.description:
Salt lakes have a unique way of preserving moments in time. I‚Äôm always on the hunt for unusual salt lakes. After hours of scouring google maps in search of anything unique, something caught my eye. A small salt lake in the middle of nowhere with what looked like a fallen tree in the centre of it. Since the object was so small on google maps I couldn‚Äôt be 100% sure if it was definitely a tree, but my interest had been peaked and I knew I wanted to see it in person.

After countless hours of driving into the western Australian outback, I arrived to the salt lake. To my excitement, there was a perfectly intact fallen tree laying amongst the pink salt lake. The thought of the tree being there for years, slowly being reclaimed by nature and preserved in the salt is what was so captivating about this spot.

data.name: ABSORBING PEACE
data.description: This work is done in 2014 in watercolors. Sometimes in our lives we go through a very low phase in our life when we need some motivation & salvation to restore back faith and positive intent in our life. During this work i had a small accident and i was completely confined to my room, where art was the rescue for me to bring the positivity. There are some memories in our life which we never forget,some of them when i faced during creating this work. The final result of this not only motivated me but brought back the enthusiasm of creativity in me. It took me 17 days to create this work. But i enjoyed the process completely and i slowly recovered from the injuries of my accident to simultaneously . Art is sometimes not only a healer but a path shower for many of us in our life. Its truly our each work is a part of our life, sorrows & pain . I am really proud of this work and it is source of light for me.  The size of this work is 34 MB. data.name: Mesmerized
data.description:
The ever evolving sense of being a part of the remotest of places, with the sound of Nature engulfing the senses and sending conscience into the abyss of darkness. A place which just a few hours ago seemed the epitome of serenity, is now filled with mystery and shadows, and yet it still becomes even more captivating than before.

The cold was intense but the weather forecast was promising, so a decision was made to stay at this off- the-beaten path spot, waiting for the dance of the Northern Lights. 

Beautiful pine trees are still an uncommon sight in Iceland, due to intense human deforestation centuries ago, but you can still find natural forest havens like these, which become even more captivating when adorned with the magic of the Aurora Borealis. 

Single long exposure photo: 30 seconds exposure. 

Collector will get a higher resolution version and/or physical print upon request. 

10% profits donated to Give Back to Nature Reforestation Project.

data.name: Reverence
data.description:
This image was captured at the end of a continuous 36 hours shooting session in Iceland. This image was shot right before sunrise, showing the unreal Vestrahorn mountains in Iceland. 

With the soul filled to the brim but the body screaming for rest, I finally crashed and slept all day inside the car after this marathon.

While doing something you love, when your body reaches the limit of exhaustion, and yet your face just can‚Äôt stop smiling, you finally know you have found "meaning"...

Technique: Single long exposure photo with tripod - 30 seconds exposure.

Collector will get the higher resolution version and/or physical print upon request.

I fully believe in a symbiotic relationship with all my collectors, hoping to establish an everlasting connection for the future. My images will always be scarce and, after 18 years of photography, I know I will never stop creating and honoring the craft.

10% profits donated to Give Back to Nature Reforestation Project.

data.name: From Chaos To Serenity
data.description:
Massive amounts of extremely turbulent waters suddenly meet the endless abyss of Dettifoss waterfall in Iceland, with liquid chaos ensuing right after the fall. 

The Universe seems to have its strange ways of always creating order out of chaos, and witnessing such water apocalypse giving birth to a steady and serene undulating river, makes me wonder if this isn't surprisingly similar to our path in life, often drowned in rather turbulent waters, but always hoping to finally head to somewhere less chaotic and filled with peace...

Technique: Single 30 second long exposure photo.

Collector will get the higher resolution version and/or physical print upon request.

I fully believe in a symbiotic relationship with all my collectors, hoping to establish an everlasting connection for the future. My images will always be scarce and, after 18 years of photography, I know I will never stop creating and honoring the craft.

10% profits to Give Back To Nature Reforestation Project

data.name: Panda
data.description:
A horse is a big personality. Only by understanding it, a person will be able to establish a strong and friendly relationship.

In general, all horses are a very peaceful creature, but at the same time they know how to stand up for themselves. Horses have such an attractive energy that there will not be an indifferent person in contact with this wonderful animal.

When I saw this horse named Panda, I immediately fell in love with her. She is graceful and fantastically beautiful in every way. I see trust and understanding in her eyes. Panda is an interesting and energetic animal. By all means, she will give warmth and care to its owner.

May this piece of artwork hold all of these elements for its NFT 1/1 owner.

data.name: Hello, mischievous boy!
data.description:
Children are the flowers of life. They decorate our life and fill it with meaning.

The birth of a child is an opportunity to immerse yourself in childhood again. Just think, after the baby appears, you will take the first steps together and pronounce the first words, you will go to the first grade again for the first time, you will return to the prom again. Being parents, isn't it wonderful?!

This photo is called "Hello, mischievous boy!". The photo shows a little boy of 2 years old, who is very happy with the outside world, happy with every little thing in life. His mischievous smile adorns this photo. The parents of this boy will never be bored. But I hope he will grow up to be a kind, wonderful and obedient boy.

May this piece of artwork hold all of these elements for its NFT 1/1 owner.

data.name: Finishing touch
data.description:
The wedding day is one of the most exciting in the life of any girl.

Naturally, first of all, photos from the wedding are created for memory for many years, so they should convey the atmosphere, emotions, aesthetics of the day ‚Äì everything so that you can be transported to this day and relive the brightest moments anew.
This photo is called "Finishing touch". The bride is preparing for the wedding ceremony: the bride's friend corrects the bride's dress.

In general, preparing the bride for the wedding is
the last step before family life.

This photo shows the emotions that the bride is experiencing at this moment, they are priceless and similar to those experienced by a student before defending a diploma.

Is it worth filming this moment? Absolutely, yes!
These are family photos that gain special value over time.

May this piece of artwork hold all of these elements for its NFT 1/1 owner.

data.name: Feast
data.description:
When looking for themes for the ultra-detailed treatment it helps to have a topic where multiplication of individual objects doesn't make the final result look nonsensical.

A banquet fit those requirements, so all the food of the world on a table was used, with some surprising results when you scroll and zoom.  

Look out in particular for the shiny metal tankard in the middle.

data.name: Flutter

data.name: Nastya 01
data.description: I met Nastya a few months ago when I joined the community, it's funny that we wrote messages to each other at the same time. I was attracted by her responsiveness, sincerity and support. All this I have felt throughout all these days here. That's what prompted me to buy one of her works. Subsequently, she also became my collector. In her works, she flawlessly displays the beauty of the female body, its fragility, tenderness, but at the same time incredible endurance. From the first seconds of our IRL meeting I realized that in front of me is a person close to me. She almost immediately started calling me "elk" - she thought I was much shorter and smaller, and this nickname was fixed on me. Even before we met, we decided to do this shoot, but I couldn't even imagine that all this would eventually turn into a real and strong friendship. I am glad to show you her as I saw her. With huge shining eyes and a completely unquenchable thirst for art. Fragile, but strong. Kind and empathetic.

This collection of 1/1 archive photographs of New York is a visual celebration of my 20+ years lived in this city: Its multitudes, its extraordinary scenes, and its staggering architecture, as well as a quiet elegy to its decay and rebirth.

This collection strives to be a token of sincere gratitude from the eyes of a Turkish immigrant, whose youth revolved around a deep fascination with American pop culture in the 1980s and 1990s, and a longing to belong to this city of neon and chrome.

data.name: Count Malthus
data.description:
In the old days, demon cults were not just for those who sought the dark side. but there are other groups accused of being a demon such as a scientist small cult Often assumed to be a wizard. So I use this story to reflect the present.
and when looking at the present You will see reflections like this happen, such as LGBTQ people, skin color, class, or people with different beliefs. These people are also seen as freaks. ‚ÄúOr when we look at people who are different from us A demon arose.‚Äù
So I was inspired to put these ideas into creating each Demon so that those who saw the work knew they were just like us and equal to us. or because they See the beauty in the path that we can't see like him. and he believed and chose to do so.
 And in this work, the mention of Count Malthas He is often depicted in the shape of a stork. Malthus builds towers and fills them with ammunition and weapons, an armorer of sorts. He was a supply unit for the Demons Army.

data.name: Friend in an abandoned house
data.description:
On my way home from school, I was walking that day using a different road than usual. It was an abandoned house on a quiet, secluded alley, with a battered wooden exterior and open doors and windows, so it was easy to get inside.

 I checked around in the dimly lit room until my eyes adjusted, and then I saw something white out of the corner of my eye and turned around. 
I was relieved to find nothing.

Then I heard footsteps tapping on the stairs near the entrance, and as I hurried over, I heard a child laughing.
I wanted to have the place to myself, but there was no point if there were other guests ahead of me.
With a sigh and a slump of the shoulders, I was about to leave the abandoned house when...

"Hey."

I heard a voice behind me and turned to see a girl about my age.

.
.
.

Guru Nanak Dev Ji told his disciples to lift a stone. To everyone‚Äôs surprise, there was boiling hot water under the stone ‚Äì good enough to cook food in it. However, the food kept getting drowned in the hot water pond and the disciples looked at the Guru. Guru taught them a lesson in gratitude when he asked them to offer the food to God if they want to have it. And yes, as soon as it was pledged to be offered to God, food started floating.

Now It is on every Sikh devotee‚Äôs wishlist to visit Gurudwara Manikaran Sahib at least once in a lifetime.

data.name: Reclaimed
data.description:
Salt lakes have a unique way of preserving moments in time. I‚Äôm always on the hunt for unusual salt lakes. After hours of scouring google maps in search of anything unique, something caught my eye. A small salt lake in the middle of nowhere with what looked like a fallen tree in the centre of it. Since the object was so small on google maps I couldn‚Äôt be 100% sure if it was definitely a tree, but my interest had been peaked and I knew I wanted to see it in person.

After countless hours of driving into the western Australian outback, I arrived to the salt lake. To my excitement, there was a perfectly intact fallen tree laying amongst the pink salt lake. The thought of the tree being there for years, slowly being reclaimed by nature and preserved in the salt is what was so captivating about this spot.

data.name: Ad Infinitum
data.description: Ever since I became a diver, I have been drawn to Mexico to explore the freshwater caves. I had the opportunity to dive in a hidden gem located in the heart of the jungle in Quintana Roo. I got goosebumps as I descended and became aware of the enormous depth and darkness of this cenote. The only source of light is a single beam that penetrates the depths and illuminates the sulfide cloud at a depth of about 30 meters. It seems as if the beam of light reaches into the unknown, the darkness, the 'ad infinitum'. A dive I will never forget.

data.name: Colored skin
data.description:
Sometimes soft and sometimes hard and brittle, just like butterflies. They are beautiful and colorful. And while they are free, they are very happy without realizing it!
As soon as you touch their wings, your fingers become colored. It may kill them, or if they are very lucky, they may fly back short with damaged wings. We have all been butterflies at least once in our lives ... sitting in the arms of someone who once loved us! Our body is a big wound covered with colored skin ...! 
And wounds ...
Wounds are the source of our pain. We have finally generously given our pigments to the hands of someone we love, but their emptiness will eventually kill us.

data.name: "Chris Brown Graffiti" (2017)
data.description: When an artwork speaks to an artist, there is always the potential for an homage. In this case, the PieceMaster has found inspiration on the walls of Miami, namely a piece of graffiti created by Chris Brown and Ron Bass (which marks the latter artist‚Äôs first foray into graffiti). Deft use of a variety of materials and textures allows the PieceMaster to capture and embellish the spirit of the original, which was created as an offering to the hurt and troubled Overton neighbourhood of Miami. Despite its placement and intent, the original also featured a fantastical splash of colors and whimsical shapes, all of which are set off by jagged negative spaces‚Äîthe PieceMaster has taken care to faithfully recreate the whole piece, and even the incidental elements such as piping. The creative exuberance of the original is here enhanced by a multilayered, three dimensional execution, and brought vividly to life by textural variety.
